    <h2>Ingredients</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>2 pounds chicken (thighs or drumsticks)</li>
      <li>4 tablespoon soy sauce</li>
      <li>5 cloves garlic, crushed</li>
      <li>1 teaspoon whole peppercorn</li>
      </ul>
      <h2>Instructions</h2>
      <ol>
      <li>Marinate chicken in soy sauce and garlic for at least 1 hour.</li>
      <li>Heat oil in a pot and pan-fry the marinated chicken for 2 minutes per side.</li>
      <li>Add marinade, water, bay leaves, and peppercorns. Bring to a boil.</li>
<li>Simmer for 30 minutes or until chicken is tender.</li>
